      <h1>Mentoring</h1>

      <p>
        I offer mentoring for students and early-career engineers who are passionate about
        <strong>chip design</strong>, especially <strong>RFIC</strong> and <strong>analog/mixed-signal IC</strong>.
        The goal is to help you learn faster, build a strong portfolio, and make confident decisions
        about research and career direction.
      </p>

      <h2>Who this is for</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Undergraduate / Master’s students exploring analog/RF IC design</li>
        <li>Ph.D. applicants preparing research statements, CVs, and publications strategy</li>
        <li>Engineers transitioning into RFIC/analog design or preparing for interviews</li>
        <li>Anyone who wants structured guidance and a clear learning roadmap</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What I can help with</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Homework & coursework support</strong> (signals, circuits, RF basics, design reasoning)</li>
        <li><strong>Project guidance</strong>: how to plan, document, and present an IC design project</li>
        <li><strong>Research direction</strong>: paper reading strategy, topic selection, and framing contributions</li>
        <li><strong>Study abroad & graduate applications</strong>: school/lab matching, SOP/CV feedback, interview prep</li>
        <li><strong>Career planning</strong>: portfolio review, internship strategy, and interview preparation</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How mentoring works</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Format:</strong> 1:1 online sessions + async feedback (docs/slides/code review)</li>
        <li><strong>Style:</strong> practical, structured, and goal-driven (weekly roadmap + checkpoints)</li>
        <li><strong>First step:</strong> a short intake (your background + goals) to tailor the plan</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Get in touch</h2>
      <p>
        Email: <a href="mailto:phuochuynh@hanyang.ac.kr">phuochuynh@hanyang.ac.kr</a><br/>
        Please include: (1) your current level, (2) your goal, and (3) what you want help with.
      </p>
    </main>
